5:
I saw it all. High up in the skies, you
fought the Lord of Shadow!
9:
We welcome you, great heroes.
Vesta! Raise your glasses to these
noble souls!
13:
Great heroes? "Lord of Shadow"? You
guys are straight out of some sort of
fairy tale, huh?
20:
Well, whatever. To tell you the truth,
the whole story could be a load of
crap for all I care.
23:
If you know each other, then
hopefully that means we can come
to a mutual understanding that
much faster.
28:
Please hear us out, Memram.
You and your people have already
broken several of our rules... This
place is someone else's territory.
30:
Would you be able to leave this
village behind and come with us?
We'll overlook this entire incident,
and—
34:
I'm sorry, but we cannot. The Vesta
are resolute. We will not yield.
37:
Humans lie as easily as they
breathe. I know very well how
quickly your honeyed words turn to
poison.
42:
P-please wait! I promise you, we're
telling the truth—
47:
The same light as before... It's even
stronger now.
52:
Your Oudo rings pure. I sense no
falsehoods. But perhaps you do not
realize you lie?
55:
Humans are capable of deceiving
even their own Oudo. I know this to
be true as well.
60:
Looks like humans made a mighty
awful impression on you, huh.
65: Do your people wish to fight us?
71: No. The Vesta do not desire conflict.
73:
When the time comes, we will leave
this land. Everything that we have
taken, we will return. You will be
compensated.
77:
But if you humans choose to
threaten us, we will turn our blades
upon you—without a moment's
hesitation.
83:
Welp... So much for taking a
vacation any time soon. Looks like
my plate just filled up.
88:
We're so far away now, we probably
look like ants to them... But they're
still watching us.
91:
Yep, they're on edge—even more
than before, when we were right in
the middle of their camp. It's odd.
93:
All right, on my mark, move behind
that boulder over there and cut their
line of sight. All smooth like—don't
look suspicious.
106: Wait a minute, what's going on?!
109:
The rest is up to you, Zekhel. Stick to
the plan and we should be good.
112:
Roger that. Thanks for the backup,
you guys.
120:
Impersonators? They didn't look like
us at all.
124:
Yep, those were some sloppy
disguises, but don't sweat it! From a
distance, they're perfect
doppelgängers.
126:
That just leaves Memram's
detection ability, but she has to
actively choose to use it. If she
doesn't suspect us, we should be
fine.
130:
Your skills don't cease to impress...
How exactly did you establish
contact with your operatives so
fast?!
134:
What, did you think those ladies
back there were the only ones with
fancy methods of communication?
137:
Done setting up surveillance in this
region. Everything's proceeding
according to plan.
139:
Looks like this old man's sneakier
than we gave him credit for.
143:
Well then. It's probably best that we
sit still for a while. Let's take a quick
rest before we get moving.
147: Get moving? Where are we going?
150:
To the branch of the Kaleidoscope,
of course. Put two and two
together—the moment we stepped
outside, they upped their security.
152:
There's somewhere they don't want
us going—that's gotta be the branch.
157:
Everything about you screams
"slacker," but you actually do your
job, huh?
161:
I'll take praise where I can get it, but I
really just did what I had to do to
avoid a direct military clash.
163:
If you want to avoid butting heads
with those ram ladies, helping me
out is probably your best bet too.
168:
You certainly have an...
underhanded side to you, Zekhel.
172:
Oh, stop it. You guys are killing me
here with the compliments.
181:
Ow-ow-ow! Mind watching where
you point that sword, Alk?
184:
There isn't exactly much room to
move! I shouldn't have come out
here this heavily equipped...
189:
Whatever happened to looking after
your elders? Ouch—that's gonna
leave a mark...
193:
Are we really sure that this path
leads inside the Kaleidoscope?
196:
Bit of a stretch to call it a "path,"
really. It's more like a crevice that
expanded and happened to
connect to the Kaleidoscope.
201:
There's no doubt about it—there are
clear signs that people have passed
through this area.
205:
Yep. That smell in the air is definitely
the Vesta. We're going the right way.
209:
If they left tracks, that means we will
too. Best to get this over with before
we're spotted.
213:
Oof... If I never go cave spelunking
again, it'll be too soon.
220:
I can't believe it... It really did lead to
the Kaleidoscope!
224:
So, now what? Where do we go from
here?
227:
Now we turn over every brick 'til we
find what we're looking for.
234:
This is the Kaleidoscope we're
talking about! You can't map this
place out. This is our best chance—
242:
I feel a shift coming. This is likely not
a normal one.
247:
You can feel shifts before they
happen?
250: Yes. At least, I could this time.
254:
Trust her on this.
Let's move, everyone. Don't let your
guard down.
